.el .ds Aq '
.TH daft-push 1  "daft-push 1.21.1" 
.SH NAME
daft\-push \- Push a branch, running pre\-push hooks in its own worktree
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdaft\-push\fR [\fB\-\-no\-verify\fR] [\fB\-\-force\-with\-lease\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIBRANCH\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Pushes a branch with the repository\*(Aqs shared pre\-push hook running in
the pushed branch\*(Aqs own worktree.
.PP
Plain `git push` fires the shared pre\-push hook with the working
directory of whatever worktree you invoked it from. A hook that runs
tests, lints the working tree, or reads worktree\-local configuration
therefore silently validates the wrong tree when you push another
worktree\*(Aqs branch. This command resolves the branch to its worktree
first and runs the push from there — that is the only thing it adds
over `git push`.
.PP
The push targets the `daft.remote` remote (default: origin). A branch
with no upstream is pushed with `\-\-set\-upstream` so tracking gets
configured. A branch with no checked\-out worktree is pushed from the
current directory, like plain `git push`.
.PP
Single\-branch only: git fires pre\-push once with one working directory,
so worktree\-correct hook context is only well\-defined for one branch.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-verify\fR
Skip the repo\*(Aqs pre\-push hook
.TP
\fB\-\-force\-with\-lease\fR
Use git push \-\-force\-with\-lease
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Be verbose; show detailed progress
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress non\-essential output
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fIBRANCH\fR]
Branch to push (default: the current worktree\*(Aqs branch)
.SH VERSION
v1.21.1
